Global Funds Buy Net 41.3 Million Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-05-18T03:35:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/global-funds-buy-net-41-3-million-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 41.3
million rupees ($916,556) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, fell 0.6 percent to 1 trillion rupees, or 34.6
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 4.87 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
